 January 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 21, 2013 || [[Second inauguration of Barack Obama|Presidential Inauguration]] || [[Eric Shinseki]] || [[United States Secretary of Veterans Affairs|Secretary of Veterans Affairs]] || <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/2013/01/21/3193012/shinseki-absent-from-inaugural.html |title=Shinseki absent from inaugural |date=22 January 2013 |work=[[Miami Herald]] |accessdate=22 January 2013 }}{{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 12, 2013 || [[2013 State of the Union Address|State of the Union]] || [[Steven Chu]] || [[United States Secretary of Energy|Secretary of Energy]] || <ref name=\"sotu2013\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/02/12/steven-chu-is-designated-survivor-for-state-of-the-union/|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|title=Steven Chu is the State of the Union 'designated survivor'|author=Rachel Weiner|date=February 12, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 28, 2014 || [[2014 State of the Union Address|State of the Union]] || [[Ernest Moniz]] || [[United States Secretary of Energy|Secretary of Energy]] || <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2014/01/28/ernest-moniz-energy-secretary-to-be-designated-survivor-during-state-union/|date=January 28, 2014|title=Energy Secretary to be Designated Survivor during State of the Union|work=FOX News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Miller|first=Zeke J|title=This Man Will Be Your President If The Worst Happens Happens|url=http://swampland.time.com/2014/01/28/state-of-the-union-designated-survivor-ernest-moniz/|publisher=Time|date=28 January 2014|accessdate=29 January 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 20, 2015 || [[2015 State of the Union Address|State of the Union]] || [[Anthony Foxx]] || [[United States Secretary of Transportation|Secretary of Transportation]] || <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/theoval/2015/01/20/obama-designated-survivor-state-of-the-union-ernest-moniz-sally-jewell/22051655/|date=January 20, 2015|title=Obama's 'designated survivor:' Anthony Foxx|work=USA Today}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jackson |first=David |title=O |url=http://www.nationaljournal.com/white-house/if-the-worst-happens-at-the-state-of-the-union-anthony-foxx-will-lead-the-country-20150120 |publisher=NationalJournal |date=20 January 2015 |accessdate=20 January 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121035156/http://www.nationaljournal.com/white-house/if-the-worst-happens-at-the-state-of-the-union-anthony-foxx-will-lead-the-country-20150120 |archivedate=21 January 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2| January 12, 2016 ||rowspan=2| [[2016 State of the Union Address|State of the Union]] || [[Orrin Hatch]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Utah|UT]]) || [[President pro tempore of the United States Senate|President pro tempore of the Senate]] || <ref>{{cite web|last=Shalby|first=Colleen|title=If #SOTU disaster strikes, Jeh Johnson ... or a Republican would become president|url=http://www.latimes.com/politics/la-pol-prez-designated-survivor-state-of-the-union-20160112-htmlstory.html|date=12 January 2016|accessdate=12 January 2016|publisher=[[LA Times]]}}</ref>\n|-\n|| [[Jeh Johnson]] || [[United States Secretary of Homeland Security|Secretary of Homeland Security]] || <ref>{{cite web|last=Saenz|first=Arlette|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/state-union-jeh-johnson-named-designated-survivor/story?id=36235856|date=January 12, 2016|title=State of the Union: Jeh Johnson Named Designated Survivor|work=[[ABC News]]}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2| January 20, 2017 || rowspan=2| [[First inauguration of Donald Trump|Presidential Inauguration]] ||[[Orrin Hatch]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|R]]-[[Utah|UT]]) || [[President pro tempore of the United States Senate|President pro tempore of the Senate]] || <ref>{{cite web|last1=Tribune|first1=The Salt Lake|title=Sen. Orrin Hatch acting as a designated survivor during inauguration|url=http://www.sltrib.